D5Comments: IT WAS DIFFICULT FINDING ELECTION WORKERS FOR THE 2016 GENERAL ELECTION AND MANY HAVE STATED THEY WILL NO LONGER WORK AS MOST OF THEM ARE OLDER AND HAVE PUT IN SEVERAL YEARS OF WORK. MANY ALSO STATED THAT THE PROCESS HAS BECOME SO COMPLICATED,
MANY, MANY PHONE CALLS.

POLL WORKERS ARE DIFFICULT BECAUSE SOME OF THEM PROBABLY HAVE PAST THE AGE OF PROPERLY BEING ABLE TO HANDLE THIS JOB.    FOR SOME IT IS A STATUS SYMBOL AND THIS MAKES IT VERY HARD TO GET RID OF POLL WORKERS THAT ARE NOT REALLY ABLE TO DO THE JO

WE HAVE THE SAME POLL WORKERS WHO WANT TO WORK EVERY ELECTION, WE DID HAVE TO FIND SOME NEW ONES AS SOME WHERE UNABLE BUT THAT WASN'T HARD EITHER.  OUR BIGGEST CHALLENGE IS FINDING DIFFERING PARTIES TO WORK.
DIFFICULT TO FIND AFFILIATIONS OTHER THAN REPUBLICAN

WE TRY TO FIND VOLUNTEERS TO WORK AT THE POLLS. EACH YEAR, IT’S GETTING MORE DIFFICULT BECAUSE MY OLDER POLLWORKERS DIDN’T WORK OUTSIDE OF THE HOME, SO THEY VOLUNTEERED.  NOWADAYS, WOMEN WORK OUTSIDE OF THE HOME AND IT’S GETTING HARD TO FIND PE

I POSTED SIGNS AROUND THE COUNTY AND HAD A GREAT RESPONSE TO THEM.  THAT REALLY HELPED! I THINK A LOT OF FOLKS WOULD LIKE TO DO IT BUT THEY DON’T THINK TO CALL THE ELECTION OFFICE.  I THINK VOLUNTEERS VS DRAFTEES IS A MUCH BETTER WORKER.
WAS NOT HARD THIS TIME, BUT MANY ANNOUNCED THEIR RETIREMENT AFTER THIS ELECTION. I ANTICIPATE DIFFICULTY FINDING REPLACEMENTS FOR THE DEMOCRAT REPRESENTATION.
I SENT OUT OVER 200 LETTERS AND MADE NUMEROUS PHONE CALLS  AS WELL AS RUNNING ARTICLES IN THE LOCAL PAPER.  I NEEDED 55 WORKERS FOR MY 11 PRECINCTS AND ENDED UP GETTING 50.
I NEED BOTH ENGLISH AND BILINGUAL POLL WORKERS; MORE AND MORE ARE WORKING AND DO NOT WANT TO LEAVE WORK.
IF SOME COUNTIES HAVE YOUNGER POLLWORKERS, HOW DO THEY GO ABOUT GETTING THEM TO WORK?
MOST OF OUR WORKERS ARE VETERAN WORKERS. TRYING TO FIND NEW AND YOUNGER WORKERS IS VERY CHALLENGING. THE VETERAN WORKERS, BECAUSE OF THEIR AGE, STRUGGLE WITH FULFILLING THEIR DUTIES PROPERLY.
I HAD SEVERAL WORKERS CALL IN THE 2 WEEKS PRIOR TO ELECTION & COULDN'T WORK SO HAD TO FIND NEW WORKERS WITH VERY LITTLE TIME TO DO SO!
IT IS BECOMING MORE DIFFICULT TO FIND PEOPLE THAT ACTUALLY WANT TO COMMIT THEIR TIME. HAVE GREAT POLL WORKERS THAT REALLY HAVE HELPED ME FIND PEOPLE, BUT THESE POLLWORKERS ARE GETTING TO RETIRE.
PARTY AFFILIATION

IT IS EXTREMELY DIFFICULT TO FIND POLL WORKERS. ESPECIALLY DEMOCRATS, WE HAVE A HEAVY REPUBLICAN REGISTRATION. NOT VERY MANY OF THE YOUNGER VOTERS UNDER 55 WANT TO MISS WORK AND ARE NOT YET INTERESTED IN THE POLITICAL/ELECTION PROCESS.
SOMEWHAT, DUE TO THE FACT WE DRAFT POLL WORKERS.  APPROXIMATELY 60 % VOLUNTEERS AND 40 % DRAFTEES.
IT WAS DIFFICULT IN ONE PRECINCT TO FIND WORKERS.
WE DO NOT HAVE VERY MANY REGISTERED DEMOCRATS IN OUR COUNTY SO THESE ARE EXTREMELY HARD TO FIND.
WITH MOST PEOPLE HAVING FULL-TIME JOBS THESE DAYS IT’S HARD TO FIND WORKERS THAT AREN’T RETIREMENT AGE AND ARE ALSO STILL ABLE TO DO THE WORK.
WE HAVE LIMITED DEMOCRATS IN OUR COUNTY, SO TRYING TO FIND THEM TO WORK THE POLLS IS DIFFICULT.
WE WERE FORTUNATE TO HAVE ALL OF OUR POLL WORKERS RETURN FOR THIS ELECTION.
WE HAVE A HARD TIME FINDING DEMOCRATIC POLL WORKERS.
OF THE POLL WORKERS THAT I USED IN THE GENERAL ELECTION, THREE POLL WORKERS HAVE CONTACTED ME AND ASKED TO BE RETIRED FROM WORKING.
I HAVE MANY VALUED LADIES RETIRING AFTER THIS LAST GENERAL ELECTION- IT WILL BE HARD TO REPLACE I HATE TO SAY.
DID NOT HAVE MUCH TROUBLE
VERY TIME CONSUMING.
EVERYONE WANTED TO WORK THE ELECTION AND DID NOT WANT OFF SO THIS TIME IT WAS EASY, MIGHT NOT BE SO THE NEXT TIME.

NORMALLY WE HAVE A HARD TIME FINDING POLLWORKERS BUT WE HAD PEOPLE VOLUNTEERING THIS YEAR.  THE HARD PART WAS GETTING THEM TO DO IT RIGHT.  EVEN THOUGH THEY WENT THROUGH TRAINING, THEY WANTED TO DO THINGS THEIR WAY.

D4Comments: ALL 10 OF THE "UNDER 18" WERE GREETERS.

D5Comments: DIFFICULT TO FIND AFFILIATIONS OTHER THAN REPUBLICAN

WE ARE ALWAYS ABLE TO FIND POLL WORKERS AND YES, SOMETIMES IS DIFFICULT; MORE TIME CONSUMING WITH TELEPHONE CALLS AND CATCHING PEOPLE AT HOME.   LAST MINUTE CANCELLATIONS CAN POSE A PROBLEM BUT I HAVE ALWAYS BEEN ABLE TO REPLACE THEM.
IT HAS BECOME VERY DIFFICULT TO GET YOUNGER POLLWORKERS.  I AM A FIRM BELIEVER IN TOTAL ALL-MAIL ELECTIONS!
THE APPOINTMENT IS ACTUALLY FOR 2 YEARS SO IT WAS REALLY A MATTER OF FILLING IN VACANCIES FOR THE GENERAL ELECTION

FINDING POLL WORKERS UNDER AGE 60 IS VERY DIFFICULT.  PRIOR TO ELECTION DAY I HAD USED ALL MY SUBSTITUTES THAT HAD COME TO TRAINING TO REPLACE THOSE THAT HAD HEALTH ISSUES OR FAMILY EMERGENCIES.  WE ARE ALSO A HEAVY REPUBLICAN COUNTY SO FINDING
NUMEROUS CONTACTS ARE MADE BEFORE ALL THE ELECTION BOARDS ARE FILLED.  WHEN THE ELECTION ARRIVED, THE LIST OF SUBSTITUTE WORKERS IS VERY SHORT.

HARD TO FIND POLL WORKERS THAT ARE YOUNGER WILLING TO WORK THE POLLS.  ALSO VERY HARD TO FIND DEMOCRAT WORKERS. HAVE THE PARTY CHAIRMAN AND HIS WIFE THE VICE CHAIR THAT WORK FOR ME BECAUSE I CALLED AND ASK THEM TO FIND ME DEMOCRAT POLL WORKERS.
IT WOULD BE EASIER TO DO THE ELECTION BY ALL MAIL.
I HAVE A GOOD GROUP NOW, BUT WHEN I HAVE A VACANCY, IT TAKES SOME TIME TO GET IT FILLED.
IT’S DIFFICULT TO FIND WORKERS BECAUSE MOST VOTERS HAVE CELL PHONE NUMBERS SO THEREFORE THEY AREN’T LIST IN THE PHONE BOOK TO CALL FOR A LAST MINUTE WORKER.
IT IS BECOMING SOMEWHAT DIFFICULT TO MAINTAIN POLL WORKERS.  I DO HAVE AN AGING GROUP AND LOST MANY IN THE PRIMARY DUE TO HEALTH REASONS.  I DO HAVE CONCERNS FOR FUTURE ELECTIONS

IT GETS MORE DIFFICULT EVERY YEAR TO FIND NEW POLL WORKERS AS THE “VETERAN” WORKERS RETIRE/DECLINE TO WORK. THE MOST COMMON EXCUSES ARE: THE VOTING PROCESS HAS BECOME TOO COMPLICATED (CAN’T SEEM TO GRASP THE PROVISIONAL VOTING OR PARTISAN/NON-P
WE USE THE SAME POLL WORKERS EVERY ELECTION.  WHEN SOMEONE WANTS TO RETIRE FROM WORKING IT IS GETTING VERY HARD TO FIND A REPLACEMENT FOR THEM.
IT’S HARD TO FIND SOMEONE TO WORK ALL DAY
THE HARDEST PART ABOUT GETTING POLL WORKERS IS GETTING THEM ACCORDING TO THE  STATUTES ON THE POLITICAL PARTY MIX OF EACH RECEIVING BOARD.
POLK COUNTY IS HIGHLY REPUBLICAN SO FINDING DEMOCRATS TO FILL POSITIONS ON THE ELECTION BOARDS IS VERY CHALLENGING.
WE NEVER HAVE ANY TROUBLE GETTING POLL WORKERS
CONSIDERING THE AGE OF OUR POLLWORKERS, I CAN IMAGINE THAT FINDING WORKERS FOR THE UPCOMING ELECTIONS WILL ONLY GET MORE DIFFICULT, ESPECIALLY IF MORE TECHNOLOGY IS INTRODUCED TO THE PROCESS.
WE HAVE HAD SUCCESS RECRUITING POLL WORKERS BY WRITING COLD LETTER EACH WEEK IN PRECINCT WE NEED WORKERS AND SEEING IF THEY WOULD BE INTERESTED.  WE TRAIN MORE WORKERS THEN WE HAVE POSITIONS.
SELDOM TOTALLY EASY AS AGE IS USUALLY A FACTOR.

IT IS GETTING MORE AND MORE DIFFICULT TO RECRUIT WORKERS SINCE THERE AREN’T AS MANY STAY-AT-HOME PARENTS WHO CAN WORK THE POLLS.  MOST STAY-AT-HOME PARENTS WOULD HAVE TO FIND A BABYSITTER/DAYCARE AND IT WOULD COST MORE THAN WHAT THEY WOULD MAKE
HARD TO FIND DEMOCRAT WORKERS.

IT’S HARD TO FIND YOUNGER POLL WORKERS; MANY OWN THEIR OWN BUSINESSES AND THOSE WITH CHILDREN ARE NOT INTERESTED AT ALL. NEXT ELECTION CYCLE IS GOING TO BE EVEN HARDER AS MANY POLL WORKERS HAVE TOLD ME THIS WAS THEIR LAST ELECTION TO WORK, DUE
FEW DEMOCRATIC WORKERS AVAILABLE, YOUNGER VOTERS DO NOT WANT TO WORK.
FINDING NEW WORKERS IS PROVING TO BE DIFFICULT EACH YEAR.
THE DAY IS LONG AND MANY PEOPLE WORK OUTSIDE THE HOME AND ARE NOT WILLING TO TAKE A DAY OFF WORK.
I HAVE ONE POLL WORKER THAT HAS VOLUNTEERED TO GO TO THE OTHER POLLING PLACE SO THAT I HAVE THE CORRECT NUMBER OF WORKERS. AS IT IS OUT OF HER PRECINCT.
